HEADWORD: High-colored
<hw>High"-col`ored</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having a strong, deep, or glaring color; flushed.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Vivid; strong or forcible in representation; hence,
exaggerated; <as>as, <ex>high-colored</ex> description</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>High-embowed </ent>⟦br⟧
